<br>
Part 2:  Prelude to War<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    Corpus walked back and forth within his counsel room.  His tail swayed back and forth with annoyance.  His mithril armor clinked and clang against each other as his clawed feet scrapped across the floor.  His eyes were narrowed and his breathe was hot, letting his thin silver tongue slithered between his teeth.  <br>
    The room was dome shaped, with tapestries along the walls.  Each one depicting a piece of saurian history.  One displayed a time of peace and tranquility, of the saurian empire.. small.. yet thriving in bliss.  The Next showed red haired demon women coming down from the mountain with spears, driving back the saurians.  And the last told the story of the total eclipse which brought down the God of the Dark Moon.  His eyes turned to it with admiration.  How he wished to see his God just once.  To salute him and bow in his very presence would be such an honor.  But he could feel him.  Flowing through the very tips of his fingers.  The bloodline of V'stakk were blessed with the power of the Dark Moon.  Though not as powerful, the dark magic was more than enough in battle against the amazons.<br>
    There came a knock at the door.  He turned to the door, which magically opened through the shimmer of his eyes.  Two saurians stood on the other side with a slightly confused look, as Corpus was standing at the other side of the room whilst the door opened by itself.  Corpus smiled grimly and turned back towards the tapestries.<br>
    &quot;My powers grow as war nears usss..,&quot; he hissed.<br>
    &quot;Yess.. Emperor,&quot; the other two saurians yelped as they cautiously entered the room.<br>
    &quot;So, what have the Green Talons discovered?&quot; Corpus asked. <br>
    &quot;Much information, your majesty.  We have word that the amazons are already rallying together within the northern regions of Scynthia.&quot;<br>
    Corpus sneered slightly, turning to their directions.  He placed his hands upon the large table that sat in the middle of the room, and gazed long and hard at the saurians.  <br>
    &quot;Is that so?  Hahaha... Excellent.  Sss, let them come to usss.  They'll never make it here in one piece.  We have many posts along Sicily.. their ships will be crushed by our fire power.  Hahaha, we are destine to win.  At long lassst, our nation will reclaim the honor and land we lost long ago.  And with this victory, we may repay our god's kindness through amazon blood.&quot;<br>
    The two saurians nodded.<br>
    &quot;What of the preacher?  Has Keena gained any information?&quot;<br>
    The saurians yelped, shaking their head, uncertain. <br>
    &quot;We have yet to speak to Princess Keena yet.  She is still her quarters with the hu-mon,&quot; they chirped.  <br>
    Corpus eyes narrowed slightly, &quot;Keep close watch upon my daughter.  Her age comes with desires.  I wish not for her to grow some attraction with amazon ally.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
    Eli sat upon the large bed, elegantly decorated with silver tassels.  His hands and feet still bound by the chains attached to a large weight.  He could barely move his toes let alone plan an escape from the strange city of lizardmen.  The air was filled with a unique fragrance of roses and spices.  At first it irritated his nostril, but like some exotic drug, he slowly began to fall under it's influence.  From behind a silk covered doorway stood a shadowy figure.  Slender and sleek, with the curves of a snake.. but the attraction of Aphrodite.  For a brief moment, Eli could have sworn it was Alysia.. but he came to realize where he was:  Keena's bedroom.  <br>
    The silk drape came down with a swift swipe of Keena's clawed gauntlets.  Upon her attire was eli's robe.. or what was left of it.  It was torn into pieces, and tailored into a new top and loincloth, which fit her body quit well (Of course, Eli was a bit disturbed seeing his robe fitting a woman better than it did him).  With a hungry grin, she slithered her form to Eli's side, inspecting him with quick sniffs to his neck.  Sweat began to form upon his brow, knowing Aly would probably kill him if she knew what was going in.  But something else was on his mind as well... How could Keena, who was very human indeed, be the daughter of Corpus V'stakk?  <br>
    &quot;You're not like the other males,&quot; She hissed into Eli's ear.  &quot;You smell so much better.  Pure.  Fresh.  Smarter&quot;<br>
    Eli raised a brow and spoke with a nervous voice, &quot;T..thanks... I think.&quot;<br>
    She grinned, pushing his back against the bed.  Eli yelped much like the saurians, not liking the situation one bit.<br>
    &quot;I'm in heat,&quot; She said huskily.<br>
    &quot;Whoa, whoa whoa!&quot; He pushed himself back up.  &quot;Not that I don't think you're a very attractive girl.. but you're only, what?  16-17?  I'm old enough to be your father!&quot;<br>
    Keena snarled loudly, pressing her claws against Eli's throat.<br>
    &quot;You listen to me, Eel-eye... I am Keena, princess to the Saurian nations.  I do what I want.  I do what I please.  And if I want to mother your broodlings, then so be it.  I am in heat and if I don't become fertilized now, then I'll have to wait another year to do so.&quot;<br>
    &quot;F..fertalize?!  I haven't even fertilized my garden in 3 months!&quot; he cried.<br>
    Keena quickly shoved him back onto the bed, forcing a kiss from him.  Eli quickly pulled his head away, accidentally shoved her onto the ground.  Eli blinked, as did Keena who looked up from the floor.<br>
    &quot;I.. I'm so sorry,&quot; he whispered looking over the side of the bed.  Keena could only grin wildly, flipping to her feet and crawl back onto the bed, stalking the devi.  <br>
    &quot;How can you be Corpus' daughter if you're human,&quot; he blurted out, hoping to distract her with questions.  The princess stopped in her tracks and raised a brow.  She gave him a slight smirk and sat Indian style beside him.  Flicking a brow strand of hair from her face, she began to speak her tale...<br>
    &quot;It was about 10 years ago,&quot; she began.  &quot;I lived in a village south of Varsith with my mother.  She was very beautiful, but very poor and sold her body to support me.  Times were rough, and the Saurians took over the village.  The saurian were kind and generous to my people, sharing their wealth.  In return, they asked for assistance, and fine goods that we produced, as payment.  The villagers agreed and did just that.  Four months later, my mother became sick and died... I was left out on the street.  One day, a rabid wolf got loose within the village and attacked me.  I could do nothing but defend myself.  I killed it with my bare hands, strangling it to death..  I did not know it, but I was being watched.  With blood on my hands, I turned to see the Emperor himself, looking down on me.  He was proud and saw potential in me; As a great warrior of his army against the Amazon threat.  And so I was adopted.&quot;<br>
    Eli looked down with sadden eyes, then looked back up to her.<br>
    &quot;Tell me of the Saurian.. Their history.  What drove them into war with the Amazons.&quot; he asked.<br>
    Keena looked to him with curiosity, then looked down and away.  &quot;Long ago, the Saurians lived in peace within the Northern lands which is now amazon territory.  We were small at the time...Living in small tribes, living off the land in total balance with nature.  One day, we came in contact with humans.. Large female humans, with weapons and masks.  The saurians were frightened and asked them to leave.  The people of the tribes wanted no part of mankind, but the humans were persistent ... at first they would come down, exploring the land, as if charting it.  The saurian knew nothing of violence or war... we simply kept a close eye upon the newcomers.  Then they came once again and demanded we leave the lands.  We stood our ground and refused to leave.. But then the arrows streaked across the skies and pierced our shamans dead.  The tribes scattered through the woods as they were mercilessly hunted down and out of the lands.  We were helpless and defenseless.  Then one night, the moon's shadow came over the sun, casting it's blanket of darkness upon the frightened tibes of Sauriania.  From the shadows came the one that would grant us the strength to liberty.  Our hearts were filled with rage and hatred for the one's He called the Amazons.  He weaved his magic upon us and made us stronger, faster, and deadly.  On that day, the Saurian Empire changed.  We were no longer the tribe we use to be.  Anger filled our hearts.. And revenge was all we could think about.  So we charged into the new amazon nation, slaughtering all.  There was no mercy..  None..  But then a light dawned upon the amazons... their strength suddenly matched the saurian's power... and once again we were driven back into the shadows... Until now,&quot; She growled.<br>
    &quot;Keena,&quot; Eli whispered, placing his hand upon her slender shoulder.  &quot;We can end this war together.. There is no reason for blood to be spilled.  Time has passed and we can mend the wounds caused by both species.  You've already created a peaceful society with mankin...&quot;<br>
    &quot;But the amazons will hunt us down!&quot; she shouted.<br>
    &quot;Not if you create peace with them!&quot;<br>
    Keena paused, looking back to him.<br>
    &quot;You are certain that it can be accomplished, huh?&quot;  She smirked.<br>
    &quot;Yes.  I know it's strange to you, but I care about the Amazons and Saurians.&quot;<br>
    &quot;You must be a saint..&quot; She whispered silently.<br>
    &quot;I'm just a man.&quot;  He smiled.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    Corpus sat upon his throne, scanning over several parchments and scrolls.  Three dark colored Saurians approached the throne with a sneaking stride.  Each one had green talons and leather straps wrapped around their chests'.  Corpus raised his heads towards the guests with a smile.  Each Saurian bowed the Emperor.<br>
    &quot;Ahh.. Green Talons.  Such a pleasure to meet the elite clan of Chin.  Was your journey to Varsith a pleasant trip?&quot;  Corpus asked.<br>
    &quot;Hai, Master.  As promised, we scouted the Amazon lands on our arrival.  We wrote down the coordinates of each village we came across.  We apologies for our tardiness, Master, for we had a few run-ins with the enemy,&quot; The largest of the Green Talons spoke out with an asian accent.<br>
    &quot;Really now?  Sss, and where are these amazons now?&quot;  <br>
    &quot;Rotting away in a ditch, Massster.&quot;<br>
    Corpus could only laugh with grim pleasure, as the Green Talon unraveled a bag filled with Amazon heads.<br>
    &quot;You have done well, Green Talons.  You will be rewarded greatly for your courageous acts.  Go now.. Eat, rest, and get ready.  War will be upon us soon.  We will need all the help we can get against the filthy mammals.&quot;<br>
    Each of the Talons bowed in respect and walked out in a single filed line.  Before Corpus could reach out and grasp one of the heads out of the bag, Keena appeared beside him.  Corpus hissed lowly, turning towards his daughter, and barked angrily, as his moment of glory was rudely disturbed.<br>
    &quot;My Emperor,&quot; She began.  &quot;I have a request..&quot;<br>
    Corpus growled and demanded what she wanted.<br>
    &quot;I have information, which I gathered from the priest.  He says that the amazons will not attack as long as we declare peace with them.  Let us declare peace with the nation of the beast women.  We've done well without war so far.  The Odusians are no threat to us and live along upon the shores of Greece.  We can set up a treaty to get back my husband to be, Ambassador Sslithe... an exchange... Hu-mon for Saurian.&quot;<br>
    Corpus couldn't believe what he was hearing.. It was blasphemy to his ears (If he had any) and was just about to strike her down when something clicked into his mind.  Suddenly a smile curled from his snout and he nodded his head.<br>
    &quot;Yesss... A treaty.  For peace.  Of course, my precious.  We will do just that..&quot;<br>
    Keena smiled brightly and hugged her father, and ran back to her room to tell Eli the news.  As she left, a Saurian Noble stepped out of the shadows and towards Corpus' side.<br>
    &quot;Are we declaring peace with the Enemy?&quot; The Noble asked with a bit of disappointment in his voice.<br>
    &quot;Do not be stupid,&quot; growled the Emperor.  &quot;Sss.. Let those filthy mammals think we wish peace.. and when they turn their back...  We'll rip out their spines!  I will not give up so soon.  Victory is on our side.  We will not disappoint our god again!!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
