<br>
&quot;Welcome sisters!&quot; She yelled.<br>
<br>
&quot;We are going up against a great enemy. One that has existed since our fore-mothers begot this Nation. My tribe! They destroyed many of our fore-mothers. . . They have attacked our allies, attacked our children in Athens! And now they have kidnapped my husband.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sighed merely thinking. ..<br>
<br>
&quot;As much as I hate waging war on others, now is the time to fight back against these creatures! One weak link in the Amazon Nation will tear us apart. I will not be that weak link!&quot;<br>
<br>
Every day she was looking more like the warrior she had grown up to be, more like the Samsara that she was, and less like the wife of the Avatar. <br>
<br>
&quot;A great Amazon once said, 'Do not sacrifice your lives for the Amazon Nation, Make our enemies sacrifice theirs!&quot;<br>
<br>
As she was about to raise her sword in the air, a large arrow flew by her at warp speed, slightly hitting the side of her arm grazing the skin gently almost cutting it. Alysia eyes looked to the post the arrow hit as a large scroll dropped from it much like her war scroll had in the other villages. She dismounted her horse and grabbed the scroll reading it over with wide eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sariah! Bring out the Prisoner!&quot;<br>
<br>
Sariah nodded and unlocked the cage that Sslithe had been held in. His wounds had been tended to and he was fed as well. Alysia was a Queen and a Warrior, not one to torture unless needed. Alysia looked to the Saurian as Sariah brought him out clad in chains to keep him still. <br>
<br>
&quot;It seems they want you back Saurian.&quot; She knew he had a name, but as long as he called her human, she would call him Saurian.<br>
<br>
She turned to her sisters.<br>
&quot;The leaders of Varsith have asked for a treaty. They gie us Eli in exchange for this one.&quot;<br>
<br>
Some of her sisters nodded their heads, others wanted war. When Alysia was about to make her decision, a younger amazon ran in through the gates. The girl must have been no older than 18 years old. Her hair was damp and pieces of her mask still clung to her clothing. She held one hand against her side blood still gushing out. <br>
<br>
Alysia ran to the girl as she collapsed.<br>
&quot;Eeris, what has happened?&quot;<br>
<br>
The young girl took a deep breath in trying to hold back the blood that choked her. She finally spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;We did as you asked my Queen, we were on our way to Rome to warn them.&quot; She coughed. &quot;The Saurian lands surround Sicily, near the coast of the bright colored sea.&quot; Her voice was harsh and in a light whisper almost. &quot;The group of us were almost there, crossing the boarders to Rome, when they attacked us.&quot; Tears began streaming out of the girls face. <br>
<br>
Alysia was almost crying as well. There was no greater pain than seeing her sisters in pain. &quot;Where are the others Eeris?&quot;<br>
<br>
Eeris' eyes welled up with tears once more.<br>
&quot;Dead. Beaten and beheaded. They let me live to come home, to show you what they are capable of.&quot; She began crying deeply.<br>
<br>
Alysia held her close knowing that she was so close to death. &quot;Sariah, Lily, take Eeris to the Healers hut and tend to her wounds quickly.&quot;<br>
<br>
Eeris took hold of the Queens hand and shook her head. &quot;No my Queen, it is too late for me.&quot; She looked skyward in awe. &quot;I can already see them . . . see the wolves come to take me home to the others.&quot; She spoke of the Ancients in the Lands of the Dead. &quot;But I might still be able to help my sisters here.&quot; Her voice was getting softer as death came closer.<br>
<br>
Alysia held her sister gently. &quot;What Eeris. . .?&quot;<br>
<br>
Eeris leaned in close. &quot;They spoke of their God, they called him the one that Shadowed the Moon. The Dark one who gave them their powers. Their strength.&quot; She gulped a bit. &quot;They have alliances with assasins, I dont know who . . .&quot; She smiled up at her Queen. &quot;Eli is alive my Queen . . .&quot; Tears began comming once more. &quot;They don't want peace Alysia . . . They want the blood of amazo ..... &quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
And with that . . . . the amazon died.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Alysia paused for a moment and turned back to her athelfi. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;WE RIDE!&quot;<br>
<br>
She set her dead athelfi down and mounted her horse charging out of the village gates. It would be a long ride to Varsith, but somehow, Alysia knew that they wouldn't make it there. That the Saurians would come to them. . . . <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
